          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to calculate and return the budgeted charge in dollars for a customer based on certain input parameters. The function encapsulates business logic that determines the budgeted charge, which is used in financial or billing applications."
